o%20well%20for%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20how%20oral%20arguments%20in%20the%20case%20went%20before%20a%20three-judge%20panel%20of%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Circuit%2C%20the%20court%20is%20likely%20to%20rule%20against%20TikTok%2C%20a%20legal%20expert%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20very%20clear%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%20that%20the%20court%20is%20just%20deeply%20uninterested%20in%20stretching%20the%20law%20to%20help%20TikTok%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Alan%20Rozenshtein%2C%20a%20former%20Justice%20Department%20official%20and%20current%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20Law%20School%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERozenshtein%20said%20that%20he%20believes%20the%20appeals%20court%20will%20rule%20%26quot%3Bdecisively%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcomprehensively%26quot%3B%20against%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20pretty%20in%20the%20bag%20for%20the%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rozenshtein%2C%20who%20like%20other%20experts%2C%20believes%20the%20case%20will%20ultimately%20reach%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20and%20a%20group%20of%20content%20creators%20filed%20separate%20lawsuits%20in%20May%20against%20the%20US%20government%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20law%2C%20which%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20signed%20in%20April%2C%20violates%20users'%20First%20Amendment%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20gave%20TikTok's%20Beijing-based%20parent%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbytedance-rather-close-down-tiktok-us-than-sell-report-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EByteDance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nine%20months%20to%20sell%20its%20US%20operations%20of%20the%20video-sharing%20platform%20to%20a%20non-Chinese%20company%20or%20be%20booted%20from%20app%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20signed%20the%20law%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-national-security-threat-framing-congress-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eframed%20as%20addressing%20TikTok's%20potential%20threat%20to%20national%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20as%20part%20of%20a%20foreign%20aid%20package%20and%20multi-year%20bipartisan%20push%20to%20break%20TikTok%20away%20from%20ByteDance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20concern%20among%20government%20officials%20is%20that%20TikTok%20could%20be%20compelled%20to%20hand%20over%20data%20on%20US%20users%20to%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party.%20Others%20worried%20that%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20which%20said%20it%20reaches%20170%20million%20Americans%20each%20month%20%E2%80%94%20could%20become%20a%20propaganda%20tool%20for%20the%20Chinese%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20haven't%20presented%20evidence%20to%20the%20public%20that%20either%20concern%20is%20happening%2C%20though%20Congress%20may%20have%20seen%20classified%20information%20in%20briefings%20that%20swayed%20them%20to%20vote%20for%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241e2e047-bf79-4929-b206-27a663cbcd94%5C%22%3ETikTok's%20lawyer%20argued%20the%20law%20'imposes%20extraordinary%20speech%20prohibition'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20oral%20arguments%20on%20Monday%2C%20TikTok%20lawyer%20Andrew%20Pincus%20slammed%20the%20law%20as%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIts%20effect%20would%20be%20staggering%2C%26quot%3B%20Pincus%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20history%2C%20Congress%20has%20expressly%20targeted%20a%20specific%20US%20speaker%2C%20banning%20its%20speech%20and%20the%20speech%20of%20170%20million%20Americans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPincus%20argued%20that%20the%20law%20is%20unconstitutional%20and%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bimposes%20extraordinary%20speech%20prohibition%20based%20on%20indeterminate%20future%20risks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20compelling%20reason%20justifies%20Congress%20acting%20like%20an%20enforcement%20agency%20and%20specifically%20targeting%20petitioners%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20of%20judges%2C%20at%20times%2C%20seemed%20skeptical%20of%20TikTok's%20arguments.%20They%20pressed%20Pincus%20about%20TikTok's%20China%20ties%20and%20asked%20whether%20Congress%20could%20bar%20a%20foreign%20country's%20ownership%20of%20a%20major%20media%20source%20in%20the%20US%20if%20the%20US%20were%20%26quot%3Bat%20war%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPincus%20argued%20that%20there%20would%20still%20be%20a%20First%20Amendment%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERozenshtein%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20for%20TikTok%20is%2C%20every%20time%20the%20word%20China%20is%20said%2C%20that%20makes%20it%20worse%20for%20TikTok%2C%20and%20the%20word%20China%20was%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20times%20by%20the%20judges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustice%20Department%20lawyer%20Daniel%20Tenny%2C%20in%20his%20oral%20arguments%2C%20said%20that%20the%20data%20that%20TikTok%20collects%20from%20its%20users%20is%20the%20same%20data%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20valuable%20to%20a%20foreign%20adversary%20trying%20to%20compromise%20the%20security%20of%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunist-party-god-credential-data-bytedance-tiktok-former-executive-alleges-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%20denied%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20has%20ties%20to%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Kreps%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Tech%20Policy%20Institute%20at%20New%20York's%20Cornell%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20judges%20sounded%20more%20%26quot%3Bskeptical%26quot%3B%20of%20TikTok's%20arguments%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20also%20raised%20important%20questions%20about%20the%20First%20Amendment%2C%20foreign%20influence%2C%20and%20standards%20of%20scrutiny%20that%20I%20do%20not%20think%20were%20clearly%20resolved%20with%20today's%20exchanges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20listening%20to%20the%20oral%20arguments%2C%20I%20am%20more%20convinced%20that%20this%20case%20will%20end%20up%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%26quot%3B%20Kreps%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fundamental%20challenge%20that%20emerged%20is%20that%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20pinpoint%20precedent%20because%20of%20how%20this%20particular%20type%20of%20technology%20and%20ownership%20arrangement%20intersects%20with%20free%20speech%20versus%20national%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJameel%20Jaffer%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Knight%20First%20Amendment%20Institute%20at%20Columbia%20University%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20filed%20a%20legal%20brief%20in%20support%20of%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20also%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20doubts%20the%20federal%20appeals%20court%20will%20be%20the%20last%20stop%20for%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday's%20argument%20confirmed%20what%20we%20already%20knew%20%E2%80%94%20that%20a%20ruling%20upholding%20the%20TikTok%20ban%20would%20do%20profound%20damage%20to%20our%20democracy%2C%20and%20to%20the%20First%20Amendment%2C%20by%20giving%20the%20government%20sweeping%20power%20to%20restrict%20Americans'%20right%20to%20access%20information%2C%20ideas%2C%20and%20media%20from%20abroad%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaffer%20added%20that%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%20reasons%20to%20be%20concerned%20about%20foreign%20disinformation%20campaigns%20and%20the%20data-collection%20practices%20of%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20but%20the%20appeals%20court%20should%20make%20clear%20that%20Congress%20must%20address%20these%20concerns%20by%20passing%20transparency%20and%20privacy%20laws%20rather%20than%20by%20restricting%20Americans'%20First%20Amendment%20rights.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupport%20for%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20among%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-ban-tiktok-movement-is-losing-momentum-among-americans-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20faded%20over%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20one%20in%20two%20US%20adults%20supported%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20in%20March%202023%2C%20now%20just%2032%25%20say%20they%20favor%20it%2C%20according%20to%20surveys%20conducted%20by%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20appeals%20court%20issues%20its%20ruling%2C%20the%20case%20could%20end%20up%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20where%20Rozenshtein%20also%20predicts%20TikTok%20will%20not%20fare%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20TikTok%20is%20going%20to%20get%20any%20joy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20TikTok%20and%20the%20users%20to%20win%2C%20they%20have%20to%20convince%20judges%20to%20ignore%20the%20considered%20judgments%20of%20Congress%20and%20the%20executive%20branch%20in%20the%20intelligence%20community%20about%20a%20platform%20whose%20risks%20are%20very%20real.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20just%20a%20big%20ask%2C%26quot%3B%20Rozenshtein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-justice-department-federal-appeals-court-law-ban-expert-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726515624000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e8806bd17aa3c7b2b31eea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-justice-department-federal-appeals-court-law-ban-expert-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20Department%20of%20Justice%20official%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20believes%20the%20three-judge%20panel%20will%20rule%20%26quot%3Bdecisively%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcomprehensively%26quot%3B%20against%20TikTok.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumec