2C%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20said%20the%20company%20was%20returning%20to%20how%20%26quot%3Bwe%20were%20before%20the%20onset%20of%20COVID.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJassy%20also%20said%20the%20company%20would%20shed%20some%20middle%20managers%20by%20the%20end%20of%20March.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20is%20shutting%20the%20door%20on%20remote%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Fcompany-news%2Fceo-andy-jassy-latest-update-on-amazon-return-to-office-manager-team-ratio%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememo%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20employees%20on%20Monday%2C%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20said%20the%20company%20would%20require%20corporate%20workers%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%20starting%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20decided%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20return%20to%20being%20in%20the%20office%20the%20way%20we%20were%20before%20the%20onset%20of%20COVID%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20advantages%20of%20being%20together%20in%20the%20office%20are%20significant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20further%20tightens%20the%20requirement%20from%20last%20year%20that%20workers%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-making-workers-employees-return-to-office-rto-wfh-hybrid-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon-site%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jassy%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bextenuating%20circumstances%26quot%3B%20and%20senior-leader-approved%20exceptions%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20accommodated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%2C%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20was%20not%20a%20given%20that%20folks%20could%20work%20remotely%20two%20days%20a%20week%2C%20and%20that%20will%20also%20be%20true%20moving%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20anything%2C%20the%20last%2015%20months%20we've%20been%20back%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%20has%20strengthened%20our%20conviction%20about%20the%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20this%20initiative%2C%20employees%20will%20once%20again%20be%20assigned%20desks%20at%20locations%20that%20previously%20had%20them%2C%20the%20memo%20said.%20Offices%20that%20had%20%26quot%3Bagile%26quot%3B%20desks%20before%20the%20pandemic%20will%20continue%20with%20those%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20also%20said%20the%20company%20would%20flatten%20its%20org%20chart%20by%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%20with%20a%2015%25%20increase%20in%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20fewer%20managers%20will%20remove%20layers%20and%20flatten%20organizations%20more%20than%20they%20are%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20without%20specifying%20what%20steps%20the%20company%20would%20take%20to%20reach%20that%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20Jassy's%20announced%20moves%20follow%20trends%20among%20other%20large%20employers%20in%20tech%20and%20retail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Amazon's%20five-day%20requirement%20is%20stricter%20than%20mandates%20from%20most%20other%20tech%20firms%2C%20Walmart%20announced%20this%20summer%20that%20previously%20remote%20corporate%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20would%20be%20required%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-cuts-hundreds-us-corporate-jobs-pushes-return-office-hybrid-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelocate%20to%20work%20at%20one%20of%20the%20company's%20three%20campuses%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Meta's%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20helped%20kick%20off%20the%20org-chart-flattening%20trend%20at%20the%20start%20of%20his%20%26quot%3Byear%20of%20efficiency%26quot%3B%20in%202023%2C%20when%20he%20criticized%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-might-cut-metas-middle-management-report-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagers%20managing%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Bloomberg%20analysis%20found%20middle%20managers%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-layoffs-2023-meta-tech-companies-jobs-employment-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%20one-third%20of%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20white-collar%20workers%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20are%20an%20Amazon%20worker%20who%20wants%20to%20share%20your%20perspective%2C%20please%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adreuter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Econtact%20Dominick%20Reuter%20via%20email%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20text%2Fcall%2FSignal%20at%20646-768-4750.%20Responses%20will%20be%20kept%20confidential%2C%20and%20Business%20Insider%20strongly%20recommends%20using%20a%20personal%20email%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%20when%20reaching%20out.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22afb715ae-b70f-48e5-942a-e109dadfbad2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20the%20full%20memo%20below%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EHey%20team.%20I%20wanted%20to%20send%20a%20note%20on%20a%20couple%20changes%20we're%20making%20to%20further%20strengthen%20our%20culture%20and%20teams.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EFirst%2C%20for%20perspective%2C%20I%20feel%20good%20about%20the%20progress%20we're%20making%20together.%20Stores%2C%20AWS%2C%20and%20Advertising%20continue%20to%20grow%20on%20very%20large%20bases%2C%20Prime%20Video%20continues%20to%20expand%2C%20and%20new%20investment%20areas%20like%20GenAI%2C%20Kuiper%2C%20Healthcare%2C%20and%20several%20others%20are%20evolving%20nicely.%20And%20at%20the%20same%20time%20we're%20growing%20and%20inventing%2C%20we're%20also%20continuing%20to%20make%20progress%20on%20our%20cost%20structure%20and%20operating%20margins%2C%20which%20isn't%20easy%20to%20do.%20Overall%2C%20I%20like%20the%20direction%20in%20which%20we're%20heading%20and%20appreciate%20the%20hard%20work%20and%20ingenuity%20of%20our%20teams%20globally.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWhen%20I%20think%20about%20my%20time%20at%20Amazon%2C%20I%20never%20imagined%20I'd%20be%20at%20the%20company%20for%2027%20years.%20My%20plan%20(which%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20agreed%20to%20on%20a%20bar%20napkin%20in%201997)%20was%20to%20be%20here%20a%20few%20years%20and%20move%20back%20to%20NYC.%20Part%20of%20why%20I've%20stayed%20has%20been%20the%20unprecedented%20growth%20(we%20had%20%2415M%20of%20annual%20revenue%20the%20year%20before%20I%20joined%E2%80%94this%20year%20should%20be%20well%20north%20of%20%24600B)%2C%20the%20perpetual%20hunger%20to%20invent%2C%20the%20obsession%20with%20making%20customers'%20lives%20easier%20and%20better%20every%20day%2C%20and%20the%20associated%20opportunities%20these%20priorities%20present.%20But%2C%20the%20biggest%20reason%20I'm%20still%20here%20is%20our%20culture.%20Being%20so%20customer%20focused%20is%20an%20inspiring%20part%20of%20it%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20the%20people%20we%20work%20with%2C%20the%20way%20we%20collaborate%20and%20invent%20when%20we're%20at%20our%20best%2C%20our%20long-term%20perspective%2C%20the%20ownership%20I've%20always%20felt%20at%20every%20level%20I've%20worked%20(I%20started%20as%20a%20Level%205)%2C%20the%20speed%20with%20which%20we%20make%20decisions%20and%20move%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20bureaucracy%20and%20politics.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EOur%20culture%20is%20unique%2C%20and%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20critical%20parts%20of%20our%20success%20in%20our%20first%2029%20years.%20But%2C%20keeping%20your%20culture%20strong%20is%20not%20a%20birthright.%20You%20have%20to%20work%20at%20it%20all%20the%20time.%20When%20you%20consider%20the%20breadth%20of%20our%20businesses%2C%20their%20associated%20growth%20rates%2C%20the%20innovation%20required%20across%20each%20of%20them%2C%20and%20the%20number%20of%20people%20we've%20hired%20the%20last%206-8%20years%20to%20pursue%20these%20endeavors%2C%20it's%20pretty%20unusual%E2%80%94and%20will%20stretch%20even%20the%20strongest%20of%20cultures.%20Strengthening%20our%20culture%20remains%20a%20top%20priority%20for%20the%20s-team%20and%20me.%20And%2C%20I%20think%20about%20it%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20want%20to%20operate%20like%20the%20world's%20largest%20startup.%20That%20means%20having%20a%20passion%20for%20constantly%20inventing%20for%20customers%2C%20strong%20urgency%20(for%20most%20big%20opportunities%2C%20it's%20a%20race!)%2C%20high%20ownership%2C%20fast%20decision-making%2C%20scrappiness%20and%20frugality%2C%20deeply-connected%20collaboration%20(you%20need%20to%20be%20joined%20at%20the%20hip%20with%20your%20teammates%20when%20inventing%20and%20solving%20hard%20problems)%2C%20and%20a%20shared%20commitment%20to%20each%20other.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ETwo%20areas%20that%20the%20s-team%20and%20I%20have%20been%20thinking%20about%20the%20last%20several%20months%20are%3A%201%2F%20do%20we%20have%20the%20right%20org%20structure%20to%20drive%20the%20level%20of%20ownership%20and%20speed%20we%20desire%3F%202%2F%20are%20we%20set%20up%20to%20invent%2C%20collaborate%2C%20and%20be%20connected%20enough%20to%20each%20other%20(and%20our%20culture)%20to%20deliver%20the%20absolute%20best%20for%20customers%20and%20the%20business%20that%20we%20can%3F%20We%20think%20we%20can%20be%20better%20on%20both.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20first%20topic%2C%20we've%20always%20sought%20to%20hire%20very%20smart%2C%20high%20judgment%2C%20inventive%2C%20delivery-focused%2C%20and%20missionary%20teammates.%20And%2C%20we%20have%20always%20wanted%20the%20people%20doing%20the%20actual%20detailed%20work%20to%20have%20high%20ownership.%20As%20we%20have%20grown%20our%20teams%20as%20quickly%20and%20substantially%20as%20we%20have%20the%20last%20many%20years%2C%20we%20have%20understandably%20added%20a%20lot%20of%20managers.%20In%20that%20process%2C%20we%20have%20also%20added%20more%20layers%20than%20we%20had%20before.%20It's%20created%20artifacts%20that%20we'd%20like%20to%20change%20(e.g.%2C%20pre-meetings%20for%20the%20pre-meetings%20for%20the%20decision%20meetings%2C%20a%20longer%20line%20of%20managers%20feeling%20like%20they%20need%20to%20review%20a%20topic%20before%20it%20moves%20forward%2C%20owners%20of%20initiatives%20feeling%20less%20like%20they%20should%20make%20recommendations%20because%20the%20decision%20will%20be%20made%20elsewhere%2C%20etc.).%20Most%20decisions%20we%20make%20are%20two-way%20doors%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20we%20want%20more%20of%20our%20teammates%20feeling%20like%20they%20can%20move%20fast%20without%20unnecessary%20processes%2C%20meetings%2C%20mechanisms%2C%20and%20layers%20that%20create%20overhead%20and%20waste%20valuable%20time.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ESo%2C%20we're%20asking%20each%20s-team%20organization%20to%20increase%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers%20by%20at%20least%2015%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%20Q1%202025.%20Having%20fewer%20managers%20will%20remove%20layers%20and%20flatten%20organizations%20more%20than%20they%20are%20today.%20If%20we%20do%20this%20work%20well%2C%20it%20will%20increase%20our%20teammates'%20ability%20to%20move%20fast%2C%20clarify%20and%20invigorate%20their%20sense%20of%20ownership%2C%20drive%20decision-making%20closer%20to%20the%20front%20lines%20where%20it%20most%20impacts%20customers%20(and%20the%20business)%2C%20decrease%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20strengthen%20our%20organizations'%20ability%20to%20make%20customers'%20lives%20better%20and%20easier%20every%20day.%20We%20will%20do%20this%20thoughtfully%2C%20and%20our%20PxT%20team%20will%20work%20closely%20with%20our%20leaders%20to%20evolve%20our%20organizations%20to%20accomplish%20these%20goals%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%5BBy%20the%20way%2C%20I've%20created%20a%20%26quot%3BBureaucracy%20Mailbox%26quot%3B%20for%20any%20examples%20any%20of%20you%20see%20where%20we%20might%20have%20bureaucracy%20or%20unnecessary%20process%20that's%20crept%20in%20and%20we%20can%20root%20out%E2%80%A6to%20be%20clear%2C%20companies%20need%20process%20to%20run%20effectively%2C%20and%20process%20does%20not%20equal%20bureaucracy%2C%20but%20unnecessary%20and%20excessive%20process%20or%20rules%20should%20be%20called%20out%20and%20extinguished.%20I%20will%20read%20these%20emails%20and%20action%20them%20accordingly.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ETo%20address%20the%20second%20issue%20of%20being%20better%20set%20up%20to%20invent%2C%20collaborate%2C%20and%20be%20connected%20enough%20to%20each%20other%20and%20our%20culture%20to%20deliver%20the%20absolute%20best%20for%20customers%20and%20the%20business%2C%20we've%20decided%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20return%20to%20being%20in%20the%20office%20the%20way%20we%20were%20before%20the%20onset%20of%20COVID.%20When%20we%20look%20back%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20we%20continue%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20advantages%20of%20being%20together%20in%20the%20office%20are%20significant.%20I've%20previously%20explained%20these%20benefits%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Fcompany-news%2Fandy-jassy-update-on-amazon-return-to-office%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EFebruary%202023%20post%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E)%2C%20but%20in%20summary%2C%20we've%20observed%20that%20it's%20easier%20for%20our%20teammates%20to%20learn%2C%20model%2C%20practice%2C%20and%20strengthen%20our%20culture%3B%20collaborating%2C%20brainstorming%2C%20and%20inventing%20are%20simpler%20and%20more%20effective%3B%20teaching%20and%20learning%20from%20one%20another%20are%20more%20seamless%3B%20and%2C%20teams%20tend%20to%20be%20better%20connected%20to%20one%20another.%20If%20anything%2C%20the%20last%2015%20months%20we've%20been%20back%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%20has%20strengthened%20our%20conviction%20about%20the%20benefits.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%2C%20not%20everybody%20was%20in%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20every%20week.%20If%20you%20or%20your%20child%20were%20sick%2C%20if%20you%20had%20some%20sort%20of%20house%20emergency%2C%20if%20you%20were%20on%20the%20road%20seeing%20customers%20or%20partners%2C%20if%20you%20needed%20a%20day%20or%20two%20to%20finish%20coding%20in%20a%20more%20isolated%20environment%2C%20people%20worked%20remotely.%20This%20was%20understood%2C%20and%20will%20be%20moving%20forward%20as%20well.%20But%2C%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20was%20not%20a%20given%20that%20folks%20could%20work%20remotely%20two%20days%20a%20week%2C%20and%20that%20will%20also%20be%20true%20moving%20forward%E2%80%94our%20expectation%20is%20that%20people%20will%20be%20in%20the%20office%20outside%20of%20extenuating%20circumstances%20(like%20the%20ones%20mentioned%20above)%20or%20if%20you%20already%20have%20a%20Remote%20Work%20Exception%20approved%20through%20your%20s-team%20leader.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20are%20also%20going%20to%20bring%20back%20assigned%20desk%20arrangements%20in%20locations%20that%20were%20previously%20organized%20that%20way%2C%20including%20the%20U.S.%20headquarters%20locations%20(Puget%20Sound%20and%20Arlington).%20For%20locations%20that%20had%20agile%20desk%20arrangements%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20including%20much%20of%20Europe%2C%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20operate%20that%20way.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20understand%20that%20some%20of%20our%20teammates%20may%20have%20set%20up%20their%20personal%20lives%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20consistently%20five%20days%20per%20week%20will%20require%20some%20adjustments.%20To%20help%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20transition%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20make%20this%20new%20expectation%20active%20on%20January%202%2C%202025.%20Global%20Real%20Estate%20and%20Facilities%20(GREF)%20is%20working%20on%20a%20plan%20to%20accommodate%20desk%20arrangements%20mentioned%20above%20and%20will%20communicate%20the%20details%20as%20they%20are%20finalized.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20want%20to%20thank%20our%20leaders%20and%20support%20teams%20in%20advance%20for%20the%20work%20they%20will%20do%20to%20improve%20their%20org%20structures%20over%20the%20coming%20months.%20With%20a%20company%20of%20our%20size%20and%20complexity%2C%20the%20work%20won't%20be%20trivial%20and%20it%20will%20test%20our%20collective%20ability%20to%20invent%20and%20simplify%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20how%20we%20organize%20and%20go%20after%20the%20meaningful%20opportunities%20we%20have%20across%20all%20of%20our%20businesses.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EHaving%20the%20right%20culture%20at%20Amazon%20is%20something%20I%20don't%20take%20for%20granted.%20I%20continue%20to%20believe%20that%20we%20are%20all%20here%20because%20we%20want%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20customers'%20lives%2C%20invent%20on%20their%20behalf%2C%20and%20move%20quickly%20to%20solve%20their%20problems.%20I'm%20optimistic%20that%20these%20changes%20will%20better%20help%20us%20accomplish%20these%20goals%20while%20strengthening%20our%20culture%20and%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20our%20teams.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EThanks%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAndy%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ceo-return-to-office-mandate-5-days-week-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726510431000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e87f69d17aa3c7b2b31e77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ceo-return-to-office-mandate-5-days-week