%20Powell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660ae4a23f923f7dab031b29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222741%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Board%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20speaks%20during%20a%20news%20conference%20after%20a%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20meeting%20on%20November%2001%2C%202023%20at%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20left%20interest%20rates%20unchanged%20at%20a%20range%20of%205.25%20percent%20to%205.50%20percent%2C%20keeping%20rates%20the%20highest%20they%20have%20been%20in%2023%20years.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIdeally%20the%20Fed%20will%20cut%20rates%20by%20a%20half-point%20without%20triggering%20growth%20worries%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECIO%20Mike%20Wilson%20noted%20that%20the%20bond%20market%20is%20acting%20like%20the%20Fed%20is%20behind%20the%20curve.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20defensive%20and%20quality%20stocks%20are%20worth%20owning%20after%20the%20rate%20cut%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street%20is%20bracing%20for%20a%20pivotal%20interest-rate-cut%20announcement%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20there's%20still%20uncertainty%20around%20how%20far%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20will%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20Monday%20morning%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20the%20market%20is%20pricing%20in%20a%2059%25%20chance%20of%20a%2050-basis-point%20cut.%20According%20to%20new%20research%20from%20Morgan%20Stanley%2C%20that%20would%20be%20the%20best%20possible%20outcome%20for%20stocks.%20But%20there's%20a%20caveat%3A%20it%20has%20to%20cut%20a%20half-point%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3Ekeep%20the%20market%20from%20worrying%20about%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20very%20short-term%2C%20we%20think%20the%20best%20case%20scenario%20for%20equities%20this%20week%20is%20that%20the%20Fed%20can%20deliver%20a%2050bp%20rate%20cut%20without%20triggering%20either%20growth%20concerns%20or%20any%20remnants%20of%20the%20yen%20carry%20trade%20unwind%E2%80%94i.e.%2C%20purely%20an%20%26quot%3Binsurance%20cut%26quot%3B%20ahead%20of%20macro%20data%20that%20is%20assumed%20to%20stabilize%2C%26quot%3B%20chief%20investment%20officer%20Mike%20Wilson%20wrote%20in%20a%20Monday%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20months%20leading%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20policy%20meeting%20this%20week%2C%20deteriorating%20labor%20data%20has%20persuaded%20investors%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20needs%20to%20start%20reducing%20borrowing%20costs%20to%20avert%20an%20economic%20cooldown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20view%2C%20the%20Fed%20might%20want%20to%20cut%20by%2050%20basis%20points%2C%20as%20the%20bond%20market%20indicates%20that%20monetary%20policy%20is%20behind%20the%20curve%3A%20if%20interest%20rates%20stay%20for%20higher%20for%20longer%2C%20they%20risk%20rupturing%20something%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fus%2Ffed-cut-rates-by-25-basis-points-sept-18-twice-more-2024-2024-09-10%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20analysts%20have%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20an%20aggressive%20cut%20could%20be%20the%20Fed's%20way%20of%20acknowledging%20trouble%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20rate%20cut%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20suggested%20that%20investors%20increase%20exposure%20to%20two%20stock%20cohorts%20that%20have%20historically%20outperformed%20in%20similar%20environments%3A%20defensive%20and%20high-quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20is%20due%20to%20rising%20growth%20concerns.%20Although%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20is%20signaling%20high%20conviction%20that%20the%20Fed%20will%20deliver%20a%20soft%20landing%20and%2015%25%20earnings-per-share%20growth%20into%202025%2C%20market%20internals%20show%20a%20different%20story%3A%20investors%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fsafe-defensive-stocks-ai-investing-rally-nvidia-semiconductors-selloff-outlook-2024-9%3F_gl%3D1*4e9jvc*_ga*MTMxNDIwNDI1Ni4xNjc1Njg3OTU4*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcyNjUwNjAxMC42MTIuMC4xNzI2NTA2MDEwLjYwLjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiling%20into%20defensive%20stocks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20fear%20of%20a%20deceleration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20the%20performance%20defensive%20over%20cyclicals%20has%20been%20the%20strongest%20since%20the%20last%20recession%2C%20Wilson%20noted.%20Defensive%20stocks%20include%20sectors%20such%20as%20utilities%20and%20consumer%20staples%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fem%3Egroups%20that%20are%20less%20reliant%20on%20macroeconomic%20conditions%20to%20perform%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDefensives%20tend%20to%20outperform%20cyclicals%20fairly%20persistently%20both%20before%20and%20after%20the%20cut.%20Large%20caps%20also%20tend%20to%20outperform%20small%20caps%20both%20before%20and%20after%20the%20Fed's%20first%20rate%20cut.%20These%20last%202%20factor%20dynamics%20are%20supportive%20of%20our%20defensive%20and%20large%20cap%20bias%20as%20Fed%20cuts%20often%20come%20in%20a%20later%20cycle%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Morgan%20Stanley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-case-scenario-stock-market-outlook-fed-rate-cut-ms-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726507621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e84feed17aa3c7b2b2f774%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fbest-case-scenario-stock-market-outlook-fed-rate-cut-ms-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stocks%20will%20get%20a%20b