3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fsites%2F3%2F2019%2F10%2F04163431%2Farvind-kejriwal-banega-swasth-india.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Arvind%20Kejriwal's%20surprise%20announcement%20on%20Sunday%20that%20he%20would%20resign%20as%20Delhi%20Chief%20Minister%20in%20two%20days%2C%20Delhi%20Government%20ministers%20and%20senior%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20leaders%20have%20been%20working%20overtime%20to%20reclaim%20the%20moral%20high%20ground%20and%20sympathy%20for%20their%20leader.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20be%20relying%20on%20the%20belief%20that%20public%20memory%20is%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20public%20address%20after%20being%20released%20on%20bail%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court-following%20over%20five%20months%20in%20jail-Kejriwal%20argued%20that%20the%20Apex%20Court%20had%20granted%20him%20bail%20in%20the%20alleged%20cases%2C%20even%20though%20he%20was%20booked%20under%20the%20stringent%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA).%20He%20claimed%20that%20the%20Court%20had%20given%20him%20the%20best%20possible%20relief%20and%2C%20since%20the%20trial%20and%20final%20verdict%20on%20the%20alleged%20excise%20scam%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20prolonged%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20step%20down%20temporarily.%20He%20stated%20he%20would%20not%20occupy%20the%20chief%20minister's%20chair%20until%20people%20certify%20his%20%26quot%3Bhonesty%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Delhi%20Assembly%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20A%20'Nightwatchman'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20is%20scheduled%20to%20begin%20the%20electoral%20process%20in%20January%202025%2C%20but%20Kejriwal%20now%20wants%20the%20elections%20to%20be%20held%20in%20November.%20In%20either%20case%2C%20Kejriwal%20aims%20to%20have%20what%20is%20known%20in%20cricketing%20terms%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bnightwatchman%26quot%3B-someone%20to%20keep%20the%20position%20warm%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20AAP%20leaders%20are%20working%20to%20convince%20the%20public%20that%20Kejriwal%20is%20making%20a%20significant%20sacrifice%20and%20stands%20firm%20on%20the%20moral%20front.%20Their%20main%20arguments%20are%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKejriwal%20is%20the%20first%20politician%20to%20seek%20a%20certificate%20of%20honesty%20from%20the%20public%20in%20an%20election%3B%20voters%20should%20elect%20him%20if%20they%20believe%20he%20is%20honest.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKejriwal%20is%20the%20first%20politician%20to%20resign%20after%20coming%20out%20of%20jail%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bpeople's%20court%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20highest%20court%2C%20and%20they%20will%20decide%20whether%20he%20is%20honest%20while%20the%20legal%20system%20evaluates%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20charges%20brought%20by%20the%20ED%20and%20CBI.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKejriwal%20did%20not%20resign%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months%2C%20following%20his%20arrest%20on%20March%2021%2C%20because%20resigning%20would%20have%20set%20a%20precedent%20that%20could%20embolden%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20imprison%20opposition%20chief%20ministers%20and%20break%20their%20parties.%20By%20not%20resigning%2C%20Kejriwal%20thwarted%20the%20BJP's%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20examine%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20when%20Kejriwal%20says%20he%20will%20return%20as%20chief%20minister%20once%20the%20people%20give%20a%20mandate%20to%20AAP%2C%20he%20conveniently%20overlooks%20two%20crucial%20conditions%20imposed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3A%201)%20he%20cannot%20attend%20the%20Delhi%20Chief%20Minister's%20office%2C%20and%202)%20he%20cannot%20sign%20off%20on%20files.%20These%20conditions%20imply%20that%20he%20cannot%20hold%20Cabinet%20meetings%20or%20engage%20in%20policy-making%20or%20policy%20reviews.%20Such%20conditions%20suggest%20that%20even%20with%20new%20elections%2C%20Kejriwal%20would%20remain%20a%20dysfunctional%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20conditions%20differ%20from%20disqualification%20cases%20like%20Sonia%20Gandhi's%20office%20of%20profit%20case%2C%20where%20a%20politician%20is%20disqualified%20for%20a%20specific%20issue%20but%20may%20be%20re-elected%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20knew%20well%20that%2C%20according%20to%20the%20court%20order%2C%20he%20could%20have%20remained%20chief%20minister%20in%20title%20only%2C%20without%20the%20actual%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoll%20Victory%20Isn't%20An%20Absolution%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20claim%20that%20a%20win%20in%20a%20fresh%20election%20would%20be%20a%20certificate%20of%20honesty%20from%20the%20people%20is%20dubious.%20For%20example%2C%20former%20Bihar%20Chief%20Minister%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%2C%20Om%20Prakash%20Chautala%2C%20and%20Sukh%20Ram%20were%20re-elected%20despite%20being%20convicted%20in%20court.%20Their%20victories%20did%20not%20necessarily%20validate%20their%20honesty.%20If%20re-election%20were%20a%20true%20indicator%20of%20honesty%2C%20it%20would%20imply%20that%20almost%20no%20politician%20in%20India%20is%20corrupt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20should%20have%20followed%20LK%20Advani's%20example%2C%20who%2C%20when%20charged%20in%20the%20Jain%20Hawala%20case%2C%20announced%20he%20would%20not%20seek%20public%20office%20until%20he%20cleared%20his%20name%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERunning%20The%20Government%20From%20Jail%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20claim%20that%20Kejriwal%20is%20the%20first%20chief%20minister%20to%20resign%20after%20bail%20may%20make%20for%20good%20TV%20debates%20but%20is%20not%20grounded%20in%20historical%20context.%20It%20has%20been%20an%20unwritten%20norm%20for%20a%20chief%20minister%20facing%20imminent%20arrest%20to%20resign%20and%20transfer%20responsibilities.%20Examples%20include%20Lalu%20Yadav%20in%20Bihar%2C%20Uma%20Bharti%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jayalalithaa%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20Hemant%20Soren%20in%20Jharkhand.%20However%2C%20Kejriwal%2C%20who%20presents%20himself%20as%20a%20crusader%20against%20corruption%2C%20chose%20not%20to%20resign%20and%20continued%20as%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20exploiting%20the%20legal%20ambiguities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20explicitly%20ask%20him%20to%20resign%2C%20as%20no%20such%20law%20exists%2C%20but%20their%20bail%20order%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20his%20position%20as%20chief%20minister%20was%20untenable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Kejriwal's%20arrest%20and%20subsequent%20judicial%20custody%2C%20AAP%20leaders%20claimed%20he%20could%20run%20the%20Delhi%20government%20from%20jail.%20Delhi's%20Cabinet%20Minister%20Atishi%20Marlena%20even%20held%20a%20press%20conference%20with%20a%20directive%20from%20Kejriwal%20regarding%20water%20and%20sewage%20issues.%20However%2C%20this%20claim%20was%20proven%20false%2C%20as%20Kejriwal%20could%20not%20effectively%20manage%20the%20government%20from%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20any%20student%20of%20politics%20would%20understand%20that%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20rulings%20on%20Article%20356%20and%20defection%20have%20made%20legal%20scrutiny%20rigorous.%20Additionally%2C%20destabilising%20a%20government%20is%20only%20feasible%20with%20a%20thin%20majority%20and%20significant%20internal%20party%20divisions.%20The%20AAP%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20government%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20and%20the%20DMK%20government%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20all%20have%20substantial%20majorities%2C%20making%20it%20nearly%20impossible%20for%20rival%20political%20formations%20to%20engineer%20defections%20and%20destabilise%20these%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Kejriwal%20thrives%20on%20victimhood%20politics%2C%20using%20it%20as%20a%20strategy